review_blob: chocolate, roasty, coffee, black, minimal head, medium sweetness, would drink again.

Surprisingly disappointed by this one. Not as much of a bite as I was expecting. The taste is decent but nothing to write home about. Its worth a shot because Im sure im in the minority on this one but for me im not that happy with it.
Huge hops in this beer. Bit like hell, I loved it. Had this on draft, and i couldnt get enough, great beer here.
Draft, this was a refreshing imperial IPA. It lacked a hard bite but that was actually a good thing because this beer was fantastic. Slightly different from most IIPAs but I liked that about it.
A good IPA, the hops are good but could be a bit stronger. Worth grabbing the bottle to try the series, would drink again.
Decent IPA. Nothing special, was hoping for more of a bite to it that wasnt there. Possibly an old bottle? Was expecting much better, slightly disappointed.
Big Stout. Great smokey taste, kicks like a mule. Loved it, would drink again.
Surprisingly good pale ale.  Nice hoppy flavor to is.  6 pack was cheap too, I wasnt expecting much but it was good stuff.
i had very low expectations for this beer but i was very surprised.  packs some good dark flavors. Would reccomend
Not a great IPA.  Has a weird fruity taste to it that doesnt go over well.  Hops arent very strong either, blah, pass.
beer_name: Flying Fish HopFish India Pale Ale

review_blob: Might have had an older bottle but I thought this was pretty weak for a double IPA. The taste was pretty good but the bite just wasnt there.  Definitely could have been an older bottle from what a friend said about the store.

Nice roast flavor to this porter.  Great value as well, copped a 22 for 4 dollars at the local store. Overall its a pretty good porter, and not that this matters at all but I love the artwork on the bottle as well.

One of the two to three best beers I have ever drank in my life.  This is a perfect IPA in every imaginable sense of the word.  If you find yourself with a chance to drink this you should take advantage early and often.
Great Oatmeal Stout.  Chocolatey/Smokey tones to it.  The smell is great as well.  Cant possibly go wrong with this one.
bare bones stout, slight malt/roasty taste to it but nothing special.  Not great but its drinkable. Meh, skip it or dont it wont leave an impression
Strong as hell, tasty in some ways but nothing amazing here. Actually wait this is pretty good Im drunk
Unremarkable beer. Sort of bland. Nothing really bad about it but nothing stands out about it either. I would drink it again but I wouldnt be excited about it
an okay at best stout, a little chocolatey but nothing outstanding.  Its drinkable but you can definitely do better
Pretty good porter, smokey and a little chocolatey, heavy booze doesnt really show up when you drink it, not bad
Very fresh citrusy taste, could have had a stronger hop bite, but over all this beer kicks hard and tastes great
Great macro IPA. fantastic hops and citrusy tastes. A mainstay in my rotation.
Not a great pumpkin beer. The taste is there but its not a good quality. not the worst offering but you can do better
really good stout. very chocolately and smooth. has a nice dry finish to it.
Great IIPA, nice strong hops, can at times feel a bit too raisiny or fruity but thats rare. Overall Id highly recommend this brew. Just take it slow because they can creep up on you fast

Wow, how is it possible that I have not rated this beer yet? One of my staple beers, fantastic IPA, great hops for a 6% beer. one of the best single IPAs you can get your hands on easily.  Drink them early and often.
pretty crappy beer. wouldnt recommend or drink again unless it was out of necessity.
Is there a difference between this and coors light? Its possible but I cant taste it. Either way drink a thousand of them and dont complain you know what its for.
Ok brew, you can drink a ton of them, nothing too special here, move along.
solid black ipa, slight citrusy bite to it though it is fairly weak. Id give it a shot again, not bad for a canned brew
weak beer, smells good, tastes ok, nothing great, but for what it is I guess its respectable, Id stay away overall
Solid Fruit beer. Strong raspberry taste and smell, harsh alcohol aftertaste to it as well though which wasnt great. Ok beer, nothing great
BOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO THIS BEER, NO THANKS AT ALL, I dont know if its the ingredients being crappy or if I just cant like blue moon beers but ugh not a fan
beer_name: Blue Moon Honey Moon Summer Ale

review_blob: Im not a big Hefeweizen drinker but this one is pretty good. The banana aftertaste is both barely noticable and somehow extremely pleasant. Give this a try for sure.
pretty solid IPA. Growler from the brewery. These guys brew a solid beer, nice place to visit, beer travels well in the growlers. IPA has decent hops and citrusy aroma, go for it
meh, ok beer, not very good for an oatmeal stout, probably wouldnt buy again, not a lot to the beer, i wouldnt really recommend
sub-standard IPA, hops are too subtle and the bite is barely noticable. I may have gotten a bad case but if not I probably wouldnt buy again
beer_name: 21st Amendment Brew Free or Die IPA

review_blob: 3 Oz sample at Bonnaroo. Really great porter, very roasty and chocolatey tastes, still was light enough to drink in the heat. I love this beer and wished I could find it up north, great porter

12 oz cup at where else? Bonnaroo...Fairly simple beer, had some light fruity tastes to it, nothing particularly overwhelming. Finished light. Not a spectacular beer but it did suit your beer needs at something as hot as Bonnaroo, glad I tried it.
mediocre IIPA, for a beer with this high of an ABA i would have expected better taste and better aftertasted. nothing special of note. not bad per say, but just un spectacular in general

an OK IIPA. Not impresse with the aroma, taste, or aftertaste, Citrus is there but not as strong as I would have hoped. Its a decent IIPA, maybe Id recommend this for someone who was looking for a lighter IIPA. Maybe the bottle I got was old
Wow, great IIPA.  Very bitter, very citrusy, hides a nice ABV well. If youre a hop head such as myself you would be wise to scoop this up if you have the offer. Well done brew
amazing black IPA. Usually im not a fan of black IPAs, i feel they lack aroman and bite, not the case here, great IPA in general. Do it.
beer_name: Stone Sublimely Self Righteous Black IPA

review_blob: wow, really good stout. Great chocolately coffee taste. Amazing value, must buy. do it

im a little torn on this one, on the one hand, as an IPA its solid, a bit more than mild, but the taste is very good. On the other hand I am very let down by the claims of coffee taste in this beer as i taste none.  A solid buy as an IPA, but youre not getting anything special as they like to claim
beer_name: Mikkeller Koppi Tomahawk x Guji Natural Coffee IPA

review_blob: awesome IPA, very fresh tasting, very bitter and citrusy. would recommend to anyone who is into IPAs

Pretty good IPA.  Not the best Ive ever had, I would have liked more bite to it. However it was very smooth and I still enjoyed it for the most part, Id recommend it even though its not a top tier IPA.
This is a great great stout, Must buy anytime you can grab it. I love everything about it. Great taste, great smell, really just an awesome beer

Great light beer, if youre at a bar and you need to slug down a bunch of beers and you cant get your hands on anything better you wont be disappointed that you get a miller lite. Its never something that you will enjoy like a good guinness or IPA but its good for what it does...gets ya drunk at a refreshing pace

Pretty good Double IPA, bit, but I was hoping for it to bite a little bit harder. The taste was very good and Id definitely drink it again, i was slightly underwhelmed but that was probably due to high hopes
EBF beer, Great stout! I kept coming back for more of this bad boy at NotB, if you can get this buy as much as possible, its incredible.
beer_name: Founders Backstage Series # 2: CBS (Canadian Breakfast Stout)
